Notebook[{
Cell["Continuous functions on a closed interval", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"8e7f6b66-0d07-4a1a-aebb-ee9116b17988"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Continuous functions are NOT part of this library's real-number theory \
\[Dash] ",
 "in the Lean blueprint they are the next chapter. But the point-set topology \
we ",
 "already have (open / closed / compact / connected) makes the classical \
theorems ",
 "on a closed interval fall out cheaply. Everything below is kernel-checked, \
0-sorry, ",
 "and lives in the demo file ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"demos", "/", 
   RowBox[{"Continuous", ".", "wl"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fddfc5c8-eacd-4636-b6ad-bb60f44023b6"],
 ". Evaluate the ",
 "cells top to bottom (Shift+Enter)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e22f3d8e-ec39-49a7-8b06-c8852eedc171"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"68165c51-396e-4c6d-96f8-b824758fe125"],

Cell["\<\
Load the kernel + stdlib snapshot and the continuity development:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"31b52238-a2cb-45fe-990e-ee40515fc68e"],

Cell["\<\
(* Load the kernel + stdlib snapshot, then the (demo) continuity theory. *)
root = ParentDirectory[NotebookDirectory[]];
Global`$HOLEncapsulationMode = \"Stable\";
Get[FileNameJoin[{root, \"bootstrap.mx\"}]];
$ContextPath = Join[
  Select[Contexts[], StringMatchQ[#, \"HOL`*\"] && ! StringContainsQ[#, \
\"Private`\"] &],
  $ContextPath];
Get[FileNameJoin[{root, \"demos\", \"Continuous.wl\"}]];
$ContextPath = Prepend[$ContextPath, \"HOL`Demos`Continuous`\"];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"cb8c9218-1edf-4a45-95c9-be1ba8443354"],

Cell["1. Continuity, topologically", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9dec3752-bd1c-4b24-9438-6fca544b7cb3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We use the topological definition: f is continuous when the preimage of \
every ",
 "open set is open. No epsilons, no limits \[Dash] just ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "isOpen"],ExpressionUUID->"8741e7aa-e097-4191-8b8a-91caae812c2e"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "PREIMAGE"],ExpressionUUID->"bf19d7a6-df11-4ffb-b9db-ae0be6918494"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"78778cee-7f52-4512-ba24-c0c8e313f1a7"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousDefThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"be879077-9006-4b3b-8d65-400e37a57bfc"],

Cell["2. The two image theorems", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0b21900b-e82b-4d02-90a5-627c65e2c643"],

Cell["\<\
The continuous image of a compact set is compact (pull an open cover of the \
image back through f, take a finite subcover, push it forward):\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d7b2f968-01a5-4e80-a8fa-294f9a3678ab"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousImageCompactThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7c55aa61-e6e7-4f12-a90a-e9b1e45da21e"],

Cell["\<\
The continuous image of a connected set is connected (a separation of the \
image pulls back to a separation of the domain):\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"de1012c0-4dc0-430f-abd8-7bed3b565c21"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousImageConnectedThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"eb1b210e-fa4b-4dd9-be36-9ade20a5cc04"],

Cell["3. A closed interval is compact", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"df0ac10c-31b5-47ba-9d59-be9521933035"],

Cell["\<\
[a,b] is closed (Topology) and bounded (lo=a, hi=b), hence compact:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"39643c5d-c913-4625-8400-c1bc74d4b412"],

Cell["formatThm[closedIntervalCompactThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"eda3579d-19d5-4b33-b55e-67740dd6964f"],

Cell["4. Boundedness on [a,b]", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b193ce4d-f5e6-4aaa-bca0-2b2bbabf2655"],

Cell["\<\
[a,b] is compact, so its continuous image is compact, hence closed and \
bounded \[Dash] in particular bounded. A continuous function on a closed \
interval is bounded:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ae23761d-42c8-4969-a151-b2fdbcbb8e47"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousImageBoundedThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"35d610ef-5d5a-4e5b-9767-036185b3ad3a"],

Cell["5. The intermediate value theorem", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6c951954-1821-4b19-bc04-2f3439f04cfc"],

Cell["\<\
[a,b] is also connected, so its continuous image is connected, hence an \
interval. Since the image contains f(a) and f(b), it contains every value \
between them \[Dash] the function-form IVT, proved from pure topology with no \
continuous-function analysis:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bd3ae424-fa8f-49a8-9878-6cb5f5eafd71"],

Cell["formatThm[continuousIVTThm]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"815a5a0a-811b-45af-8c25-213026fde576"],

Cell["A live check", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"e957f702-1668-447b-a035-6f7aaa7b488b"],

Cell["\<\
Each statement above is a real theorem object; the kernel built it. For \
example, the IVT has no hypotheses beyond the ones shown, and is genuinely a \
theorem:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4b206688-04c1-4eb6-bcfc-3928b4f13bff"],

Cell["{isThm[continuousIVTThm], hyp[continuousIVTThm]}", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"eea53869-d2ad-4390-a655-ea7e6adc9886"],

Cell["Next steps", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"cb5cb0b6-56d3-440f-ad5a-9e4d08a518f1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "See ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"demos", "/", 
   RowBox[{"Continuous", ".", "wl"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4b6016f4-754d-42a0-9aed-ad881c877c89"],
 " for the proofs and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"docs", "/", 
   RowBox[{"USER_GUIDE", ".", "md"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "215527fd-6ca6-4b5f-834a-1bcd5cb06243"],
 " for the API."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"80f5977d-eb21-4783-bfcd-7d2a8a622c55"]
},
WindowSize->{820, 720},
